Your command line parameters for perl.exe are probably:
	1.)	-e
	2.)	"$a="
	3.)	A
	4.)	" x 256; system($a)"

Thus are you sure you get $A set with 256 "A"s?

Are you crashing system() or perl.exe's command line parser?

Please define "crashed".

